WEBVTT

00:01.002 --> 00:02.503
NARRATOR:
Previously on Prison Break .'

00:02.670 --> 00:06.174
A very credible witness has just come
forward and he's willing to testify.

00:06.340 --> 00:09.135
He'll corroborate everything
you've said about this conspiracy.

00:09.302 --> 00:10.720
Who?

00:12.388 --> 00:15.391
How much do you know
about Sona, Mr. Kim?

00:15.558 --> 00:19.353
Only what I've been given clearance on.
There's been a change in strategy.

00:19.520 --> 00:22.857
- How much further would I have to go?
- For this you only have to go to Panama.

00:23.024 --> 00:25.776
- I didn't know you'd be here.
- You e-mailed me, said T-Bag was here.

00:25.985 --> 00:28.070
- It's on the website.
- I didn't write on no website.

00:28.237 --> 00:31.657
- This is looking more like a setup.
- He's got Maricruz locked away.

00:31.824 --> 00:34.160
Either I help him get the money
or she's dead.

00:34.327 --> 00:36.120
Freeze, Bagwell!

00:36.287 --> 00:38.039
[GUNSHOTS, THEN SCREAMING]

00:38.206 --> 00:41.584
Theodore Bagwell. He's the one
you want for that dead chick in there.

00:41.751 --> 00:43.461
MICHAEL:
Sucre, you better pull it together.

00:43.628 --> 00:44.837
SUCRE:
Oh, God!

00:46.255 --> 00:48.174
Go get the money. Please.

00:49.592 --> 00:50.927
Who you fooling?

00:51.093 --> 00:54.096
You ain't gonna kill me,
Mr. Michelangelo.

00:54.263 --> 00:55.598
You ain't got it in you.

00:55.765 --> 00:57.767
[SCREAMING]

00:59.435 --> 01:00.937
- Linc:?
- Hello, Michael.

01:01.395 --> 01:02.855
<i>MICHAEL:
What do you want, Alex?</i>

01:03.022 --> 01:04.857
Bring me the money. Bring me the boat.

01:05.024 --> 01:06.567
You are out of your mind.

01:06.734 --> 01:08.527
We have something
the other person needs.

01:08.694 --> 01:10.404
<i>Your brother for your plan.</i>

01:10.571 --> 01:13.366
Five minutes. That's what you have.

01:23.626 --> 01:24.877
<i>UNCOLN:
I didn't kill that man.</i>

01:26.379 --> 01:27.964
<i>MICHAEL:
I'm getting you out of here.</i>

01:28.130 --> 01:30.800
LINCOLN: / <i>got three weeks.
MICHAEL: Just have a //tt/e faith.</i>

01:33.803 --> 01:35.596
<i>I did everything I could.</i>

01:35.763 --> 01:37.139
<i>UNCOLN:
I know you did.</i>

01:50.987 --> 01:52.822
MAN:
Sefior.

01:53.656 --> 01:56.701
- Chicle?
- No.

01:56.867 --> 01:59.245
Soda? Beer, my friend.

02:00.538 --> 02:03.082
Spleef? Magic mushrooms.

02:03.249 --> 02:05.084
Burst your brain, split it wide open.

02:06.294 --> 02:07.962
I'm your man, man.

02:08.128 --> 02:10.172
Magic Mystery Tour,
right here in this box.

02:10.339 --> 02:13.175
If I don't got it, I can get it.

02:13.342 --> 02:14.427
[PHONE RINGING]

02:14.593 --> 02:15.845
Beat it.

02:20.850 --> 02:23.185
<i>MAHONE</i> [OVER <i>PHONE]: <i>
80 you gonna do the right thing?</i></i>

02:24.562 --> 02:25.980
Right for who, Alex?

02:26.856 --> 02:28.190
<i>You've lost, Michael.</i>

02:28.357 --> 02:29.692
That's what you've done here.

02:29.859 --> 02:33.863
You'll lose a whole lot more unless
you tell me right here and right now...

02:34.030 --> 02:37.158
...you're gonna bring me the money,
you're gonna bring me the boat.

02:37.325 --> 02:40.036
And you'll just let my brother go.

02:40.536 --> 02:41.787
Yeah.

02:41.954 --> 02:47.209
Just like you let Tweener go
and Abruzzi and Haywire.

02:47.376 --> 02:49.295
Things are different now.

02:49.462 --> 02:51.047
- Really?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

02:51.213 --> 02:56.719
The people I was working for,
they kind of, uh, sold me down the river.

02:56.886 --> 02:59.138
Now I just wanna go out to sea.

02:59.305 --> 03:01.349
That's funny.
I'll have to remember that one.

03:01.515 --> 03:04.060
I face more prison time than you.

03:04.226 --> 03:07.563
Sort of jumped ahead of you a few
spots on the public enemy list.

03:08.522 --> 03:11.067
You're my way to freedom, Michael,
and I'm yours.

03:11.233 --> 03:13.235
<i>We both know
what the other one's capable of.</i>

03:13.402 --> 03:16.405
<i>Let's treat each other with respect here.
No games, no bluffing.</i>

03:16.572 --> 03:19.075
Just two guys
doing each other a favor.

03:19.241 --> 03:21.243
<i>What do you say?</i>

03:23.746 --> 03:25.206
Where are you?

03:25.373 --> 03:28.250
Mira Flores shipping docks,
just outside of Panama City.

03:28.417 --> 03:31.170
It's a big warehouse
right on the water.

03:31.337 --> 03:32.922
That's a long ways.

03:33.089 --> 03:35.091
It'll take me at least 24 hours
to get there.

03:35.883 --> 03:38.219
Well, then, I'd get moving.

03:41.680 --> 03:44.016
LINCOLN:
How's it feel being on the run?

03:44.517 --> 03:47.103
<i>- I'll</i> survive.
- Not if they catch you.

03:47.728 --> 03:49.105
They'll send you to the chair.

03:50.940 --> 03:52.525
You think that's ironic?

03:52.691 --> 03:54.568
It'd be justice.

03:54.735 --> 03:56.278
Mr. Kim. Alex Mahone.

03:57.863 --> 03:59.281
Call me.

03:59.448 --> 04:03.119
Oh, justice will be served.

04:05.371 --> 04:09.959
What I'm about to divulge to you
will in all likelihood get me killed.

04:10.126 --> 04:13.462
- Actually, I guarantee it.
- Then why are you doing it?

04:15.297 --> 04:18.634
Because this was supposed to be
about country, about loyalty...

04:18.801 --> 04:21.220
...about what's right, but it wasn't.

04:21.387 --> 04:26.142
Because I wronged people
who should not have been wronged.

04:31.647 --> 04:34.316
Those orders were given
by Caroline Reynolds...

04:34.483 --> 04:36.735
...who was vice president at the time.

04:36.902 --> 04:40.823
Acting on those orders,
I planted evidence.

04:40.990 --> 04:46.120
I procured a body, I lured Lincoln Burrows
into that parking garage that evening...

04:46.287 --> 04:48.747
...under the auspices of a different hit.

04:51.917 --> 04:54.670
From the ground up, we framed him.

04:58.174 --> 04:59.425
Perfect.

04:59.592 --> 05:03.012
See, Lincoln Burrows gets executed,
people forget about Terrence Steadman...

05:03.179 --> 05:05.598
...the controversy surrounding him
and the presidency.

05:05.764 --> 05:08.934
And nobody ever knows
about the Company.

05:09.101 --> 05:12.313
Yes, which is a shadowy cabal
of corporations...

05:12.480 --> 05:16.025
...that pretty much influence everything
that happens in this country.

05:16.192 --> 05:19.695
But I fail to see how any of this
is relevant to Sara Tancredi...

05:19.862 --> 05:22.781
...and the fact that she aided and
abetted, that she jumped bail.

05:22.948 --> 05:26.660
She did so because she feared
for her life, which was appropriate...

05:26.827 --> 05:28.787
...as I had orders to kill her.

05:29.747 --> 05:32.208
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

05:35.461 --> 05:37.129
[GAVEL BANGING]

05:52.394 --> 05:54.230
Hey-

05:57.900 --> 05:59.652
You still in the magic business?

06:00.069 --> 06:01.487
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

06:01.654 --> 06:04.406
- What's your name?
- Chaco.

06:05.908 --> 06:07.493
<i>JUDGE".
It's all here.</i>

06:07.660 --> 06:11.121
Everything Mr. Kellerman said
is corroborated in these documents.

06:11.330 --> 06:14.083
In light of this evidence,
my question, I guess to you...

06:14.250 --> 06:16.752
...is whether your time
and resources are best spent...

06:16.919 --> 06:19.338
...in pursuing charges
against Dr. Tancredi.

06:20.172 --> 06:24.927
No. My office will drop all charges
effective immediately.

06:26.554 --> 06:29.431
But, Your Honor, I would like
to devote my time and attention...

06:29.598 --> 06:33.477
...in prosecuting this man,
Mr. Kellerman.

06:33.644 --> 06:35.729
JUDGE:
Officer.

06:41.068 --> 06:44.280
I literally don't even know
what to say to you.

06:45.364 --> 06:47.825
It was good knowing you, Sara.

06:51.620 --> 06:53.789
[PHONE RINGS]

06:55.916 --> 06:57.918
- Yeah?
- Where are we?

06:58.085 --> 06:59.628
<i>I'm in Panama. Nice place.</i>

07:00.421 --> 07:02.423
Good weather. Cool breeze.

07:02.590 --> 07:04.466
Where are we with the brothers?

07:05.301 --> 07:08.470
<i>When you get them, I wanna
come down there for confirmation.</i>

07:08.637 --> 07:10.055
<i>I suggest you get on a plane.</i>

07:10.222 --> 07:11.390
By the time you get here...

07:11.557 --> 07:14.059
...I'll have Scofield and Burrows
where you want them.

07:14.226 --> 07:16.604
And then this whole thing is over.

07:29.491 --> 07:30.993
MICHAEL:
Sara, it's me.

07:31.160 --> 07:33.287
It's a strange thing...

07:33.996 --> 07:37.499
...leaving a message for someone
you know is never gonna get it.

07:39.251 --> 07:40.669
I can only assume the worst...

07:40.836 --> 07:45.799
...so this'll be the last message
I'll leave for you.

07:47.760 --> 07:50.512
I just wanted you to know
that I made it.

07:52.681 --> 07:55.017
But it's no good without you.

07:59.021 --> 08:01.106
Anyway, remember when l...?

08:01.273 --> 08:04.193
Remember when I told you
about those 50-cent beers...

08:04.360 --> 08:07.237
...in Baja at happy hour?

08:08.030 --> 08:10.115
Well, they're even cheaper down here.

08:10.824 --> 08:13.827
And if by some miracle
you do get this...

08:15.204 --> 08:17.748
...I need you to listen close.

08:19.708 --> 08:23.921
Sara. Sara, I suggest
we get you out of here.

08:24.088 --> 08:28.384
It's gonna be a media circus outside
and it'll only get bigger. Let's go.

08:29.301 --> 08:30.678
Sure.

08:30.844 --> 08:36.308
<i>Larger unexpected fireworks at the trial
of Dr. Sara Tancredi in Chicago today.</i>

08:36.475 --> 08:39.852
<i>New testimony has implicated
that former President Reynolds...</i>

08:40.020 --> 08:44.525
<i>...was complicit in the falsification of
her brother Terrence Steadman's death.</i>

08:44.692 --> 08:47.361
<i>The fallout from all this,
the purported killer...</i>

08:47.528 --> 08:52.074
<i>...Lincoln Burrows, who's led
the country on a nationwide manhunt...</i>

08:52.241 --> 08:55.661
<i>...will be exonerated of all charges
effective immediately.</i>

08:57.246 --> 09:00.416
Oh, my God, Bruce.
Lincoln's a free man.

09:38.162 --> 09:42.249
Michael left me a message.
Okay. My God. Um...

09:43.917 --> 09:46.462
He doesn't know.
He's still planning on running.

09:46.628 --> 09:48.464
Uh...

09:48.630 --> 09:51.425
Come on, Michael. Come on,
come on, come on.

09:51.592 --> 09:53.260
[PHONE RINGING]

09:53.427 --> 09:54.845
Let me do the intro.

09:55.012 --> 09:57.222
Fine. Then I'll do the talking.

10:04.354 --> 10:05.606
Okay, I gotta go to him.

10:05.773 --> 10:07.483
- What's that, about 3000 miles?
- It is.

10:07.649 --> 10:11.320
We're gonna have to swing by my hotel,
and you'll have to get me to the airport.

10:11.487 --> 10:15.282
He's gotta know he doesn't have to run.
What he's doing is gonna get him killed.

10:19.661 --> 10:22.456
KIM:
The stars are finally aligning, sir.

10:23.123 --> 10:25.626
Mahone's got Burrows.
Scofield's on his way.

10:27.836 --> 10:31.423
I will make it happen.
I am going down there myself.

10:35.719 --> 10:39.723
Uh, I assume we both know
which one that is.

10:43.727 --> 10:46.522
I will call you when I get down there.

11:01.161 --> 11:04.665
MAHONE: I just-- I want you to listen
really, really close, okay?

11:04.832 --> 11:07.543
<i>PAM: Alex, Alex, slow down.
- Okay, okay, fine.</i>

11:07.709 --> 11:10.712
We talked about getting back together,
about giving it another shot.

11:10.879 --> 11:13.632
Yes, and I said that maybe we could.

11:13.799 --> 11:15.759
[LINCOLN TSKING]

11:16.885 --> 11:19.012
<i>- Alex?</i>
- What about Columbia?

11:19.513 --> 11:21.890
- Cartegena?
- Go there?

11:22.057 --> 11:24.226
<i>Well, you got summer break
coming up, don't you?</i>

11:24.393 --> 11:26.728
- Same with Cam?
- Yeah. But--

11:26.895 --> 11:28.897
Listen, I'm not far from there
right now...

11:29.064 --> 11:32.693
...and I was thinking, why not just stick
around and have you guys come down?

11:32.860 --> 11:34.987
I mean, you always wanted to go,
didn't you?

11:35.153 --> 11:38.073
- Visit the homeland?
- Yes, but you didn't.

11:38.740 --> 11:39.992
Yeah, but I do now.

11:41.493 --> 11:43.495
Uh...

11:43.662 --> 11:47.499
Yeah. I mean, I suppose I could,
we could maybe do two weeks...

11:47.666 --> 11:49.126
<i>...at the end of the summer, or--</i>

11:49.293 --> 11:51.670
- Is that a yes? That's a yes, right?
- Yes, yes.

11:51.837 --> 11:54.423
Great coffee, great beaches,
wildlife parks for Cam and--

11:55.257 --> 12:00.762
Look, it might not work out.
You've gotta be prepared for that. I--

12:00.929 --> 12:03.015
It can't be like it was before.

12:05.684 --> 12:07.853
It will never be like before.

12:08.020 --> 12:10.272
I know what's important now.
I know what matters.

12:10.439 --> 12:13.233
<i>Well, I guess I could look online.</i>

12:14.109 --> 12:15.444
<i>I don't know. I should go.</i>

12:15.611 --> 12:16.945
Just come be with me, Pam.

12:17.946 --> 12:19.615
<i>Be with me.</i>

12:35.923 --> 12:39.134
Hey, you got nothing
to worry about, okay?

12:39.301 --> 12:40.719
It's you I'm marrying.

12:44.181 --> 12:45.432
WOMAN:
Sefior Gonzales.

12:45.599 --> 12:48.644
[m SPANISH]

13:07.287 --> 13:08.830
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH
OVER PHONE]

13:19.758 --> 13:21.551
<i>MAN</i> [IN <i>ENGLISH]: <i>
U. S. Embassy operator.</i></i>

13:21.760 --> 13:25.263
I'm looking for a friend.
A missing American friend.

13:25.430 --> 13:29.142
He could be in the hospital.
He could be in jail.

13:29.309 --> 13:31.019
<i>Name?</i>

13:31.895 --> 13:35.899
Bellick. Brad Bellick.

13:37.234 --> 13:40.862
BELLICK: Hey! Hey, do I get
to call my lawyer or what?!

13:41.029 --> 13:43.407
What are you, savages down here?

13:43.573 --> 13:46.702
I get to call my lawyer or something.

13:46.868 --> 13:49.204
Freaking banana benders.

13:59.464 --> 14:01.049
Finally! That's him!

14:01.591 --> 14:05.053
That's the guy. He's the one
that killed that girl. Good job, guys.

14:05.220 --> 14:07.222
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

14:08.640 --> 14:11.351
Hey. Hey, aren't you gonna
release me now?

14:11.518 --> 14:13.228
Hey-

14:13.395 --> 14:14.604
Hey!

14:18.442 --> 14:21.069
- You're busted.
- Am I?

14:23.155 --> 14:26.324
- Where's the money?
- Pretty Boy's got it.

14:26.491 --> 14:30.704
He's out there with a royal flush, and
you're in here with a busted straight.

14:30.871 --> 14:34.583
- That hardly seems right, does it?
- Your hand don't look much better.

14:34.750 --> 14:36.460
Maybe I got an ace up my sleeve.

14:36.626 --> 14:39.087
You know something I don't?

14:41.131 --> 14:43.925
You should rest your leg, boss.

14:57.898 --> 15:00.192
[m SPANISH]

15:11.787 --> 15:13.663
MICHAEL:
I was told we could make a deal.

15:14.289 --> 15:17.334
You're a long ways from home, boy.
There ain't no deal for you here.

15:17.501 --> 15:19.753
You haven't heard
what I have to offer.

15:23.757 --> 15:26.885
A guy looking like you do,
coming here?

15:27.010 --> 15:30.013
Only thing you offering is jail time.

15:33.683 --> 15:35.644
I'm not a cop.

15:42.359 --> 15:46.321
Check online.
Type in Michael Scofield.

15:46.488 --> 15:47.989
That means nothing to me.

15:48.156 --> 15:49.783
Could mean a hundred grand.

16:02.754 --> 16:04.756
[WHISTLES]

16:04.923 --> 16:07.968
This takes longer than 3O seconds,
you're in the canal.

16:09.261 --> 16:12.055
Bait for the catfish.

16:13.348 --> 16:14.683
Hey-

16:24.651 --> 16:27.571
You just gave me a hundred thousand
reasons to turn you in.

16:27.737 --> 16:29.030
That's true.

16:30.157 --> 16:32.659
I guess I'll just have to give you
a few more not to.

16:40.083 --> 16:41.626
You know I'm innocent.

16:41.793 --> 16:44.087
- Yeah, probably.
- And yet you don't care.

16:44.254 --> 16:47.382
I don't care about anything
other than getting my life back, no.

16:47.549 --> 16:49.259
Your wife know who you really are?

16:50.177 --> 16:51.595
Hey, you know how it is.

16:51.761 --> 16:54.764
Good men doing bad things
because of circumstance.

16:55.348 --> 16:59.561
I'd call her back if I were you.
Tell her to forget you were ever born.

16:59.728 --> 17:01.271
Oh, you would, would you?

17:01.438 --> 17:03.773
Stop the cancer
from your life spreading to theirs.

17:05.650 --> 17:07.986
Cancer of my life?

17:08.612 --> 17:11.448
I wouldn't be begging her to meet me
in this third-world dump...

17:11.615 --> 17:13.366
...if it weren't for you and your life.

17:13.532 --> 17:17.996
There's no way out of this for you.
For any of us.

17:22.041 --> 17:24.085
For me, there is.

17:24.711 --> 17:26.755
For me, there is.

17:32.302 --> 17:37.599
- How much of it you spend?
- A hundred thousand. Two.

17:37.766 --> 17:39.768
Of course, down here,
be more like a million.

17:39.935 --> 17:42.437
Be Louis XIV for a sum like that.

17:42.604 --> 17:44.481
The Sun King of Panama.

17:44.648 --> 17:47.150
You ain't gonna be seeing
much sun now.

17:47.317 --> 17:50.612
Hmm. I don't know.

17:52.155 --> 17:57.661
You know, Bagwell, out of all
the guys, all eight of them...

17:57.827 --> 18:01.665
...you were the guy I was hoping
would go down in a blaze of gunfire.

18:01.831 --> 18:04.417
Why don't you give me
your best shot? Finish the job.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.336
Maybe I will.

18:09.547 --> 18:14.344
That Siamese cat smile just makes me
wanna open you up that much more.

18:14.511 --> 18:18.181
It's Cheshire. Cheshire cat smile.

18:18.390 --> 18:20.809
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

18:21.935 --> 18:24.062
I'm free?

18:29.526 --> 18:30.860
Hey-

18:31.069 --> 18:32.862
Hey, What the hell is this?

18:33.071 --> 18:36.199
Hey, wait, wait a minute.
What about him?

18:36.366 --> 18:38.076
He's the one that did it.

18:38.243 --> 18:41.079
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

18:41.246 --> 18:44.499
What's that mean? <i>Buena suerfe?</i>
What does that mean?

18:46.167 --> 18:48.169
Good luck.

18:57.762 --> 18:59.723
[m SPANISH]

19:11.776 --> 19:13.695
SUCRE:
Bellick.

19:15.030 --> 19:17.157
Bellick!

19:17.324 --> 19:19.909
Where is mi Maricruz?

19:20.577 --> 19:21.828
Where is she?

19:29.753 --> 19:32.547
You wanna know where she is,
find a way to get me out of this!

19:33.590 --> 19:35.216
Get me out of here!

19:35.383 --> 19:38.595
Sucre, get me out of this! Get me out!

19:51.733 --> 19:54.361
Maricruz.

19:56.279 --> 19:58.281
Maricruz.

20:58.258 --> 21:00.051
[DOOR OPENING]

21:04.097 --> 21:06.850
Michael, that's a beautiful boat.

21:07.016 --> 21:09.352
Just promise you'll change the name
when you take it.

21:09.519 --> 21:12.105
I don't think my mother
would have approved of you.

21:12.272 --> 21:14.232
Consider it done. Come on.

21:14.357 --> 21:16.443
- Uncuff me.
- No, not yet.

21:16.609 --> 21:18.862
So is this the part
where you go back on your word?

21:19.863 --> 21:21.698
Hands up, hands up.

21:24.617 --> 21:26.035
No.

21:26.244 --> 21:30.290
As of now, they want you alive.

21:30.457 --> 21:31.875
Why?

21:33.376 --> 21:35.336
That's a good question.

21:35.503 --> 21:38.256
Figure it out some day, on your
own time. Where's the money?

21:38.381 --> 21:40.383
- Cut him loose.
- No.

21:40.550 --> 21:42.677
Come on, Alex.
You already got the boat.

21:42.844 --> 21:45.013
- Show a little good faith.
- The money.

21:45.597 --> 21:46.931
I want--

21:47.098 --> 21:48.641
[PHONE RINGS]

21:50.018 --> 21:51.936
